Package: latexsnipper
Version: 2.4.0
Section: utils
Priority: optional
Architecture: amd64
Installed-Size: 1019920
Maintainer: Mathcraft <mathcraft@example.com>
Homepage: https://github.com/SakuraMathcraft/LaTeXSnipper
Description: Desktop math workspace for capture, recognize, edit and compute
 LaTeXSnipper is a desktop math workspace built for end-to-end math
 content workflows:
  - Capture and recognize mathematical content from screenshots
  - Continue editing and computing in the integrated math workbench
  - Handwrite expressions in a dedicated canvas and convert to LaTeX
  - Send results back to the main editor or copy to clipboard
 .
 Supports both X11 and Wayland display servers.
Depends: libc6 (>= 2.35), libgl1, libglib2.0-0, libx11-6, libxcb1, libxkbcommon0, libxcomposite1, libxdamage1, libxext6, libxfixes3, libxrandr2, libxrender1, libegl1, libopengl0, libfontconfig1, libdbus-1-3, libnss3, libnspr4, libasound2, libpulse0, libxss1, libxtst6, libgtk-3-0, libgdk-pixbuf-2.0-0, libatk-bridge2.0-0, libcups2, libdrm2, zlib1g, python3, python3-venv, gnome-screenshot | maim | grim
Recommends: pandoc, texlive-latex-base
Suggests: texlive-full, imagemagick, scrot, poppler-utils
